<br>
Dual wield for 75% damage output/100% aggro/25% defense<br>
Sword/sheild for 50% damage output/50% aggro/100% defense<br>
2h weapons for 100% damage output/50% aggro/50% defense<br>
<br>
And SK's/Pals the choise of only sword and shield or 2h weapons.<br>
<br>
The main improvement I would like for Warriors is to give them better aggro management skills so that Warriors don't have to rely on procs (or Chanter/SK buffs) to maintain aggro in exp grind situations.  Procs and buffs should be icing on the cake for raids to help with high-burn nuking, lucky backstabs/crits/procs of others.  How about making high levels of taunt skills in addition to the active hate management, automaticly increase your aggro per dps by .5, so you can be doing 2/3 the damage of a rogue/monk and still have aggro without having to rely on procs. <p><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=257207" *****"text-decoration: none">Khuzdul</A><br>
<A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=257219" *****"text-decoration: none">Ologhai</A><br>
<A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=257272" *****"text-decoration: none">Vendetta</A><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=skace>Skace</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 67<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/4/02 1:07:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2517.topic&index=42>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: How best to improve the warrior</span><hr size=1> Dual wield for 75% damage output/100% aggro/25% defense<br>
Sword/sheild for 50% damage output/50% aggro/100% defense<br>
2h weapons for 100% damage output/50% aggro/50% defense<br>
<br>
or how about<br>
<br>
Dual Weild = 100% Damage Output | 100% Agro | 75% Defense<br>
Sword/Shield = 75% Damage Output | 100% Agro | 100% Defense<br>
2h Weapons = 100% Damage Output | 100% Agro | 75% Defense<br>
<br>
See, All 3 should generate the same ammount of agro. Thus removing agro management from the type of weapon and keeping it a specific of a weapon. People shouldn't say &quot;Your tanking so you should be DW'ng&quot; they should say &quot;Your tanking so long as your weapons hold agro well&quot;. The fastest hitter shouldn't necessarily generate more agro. The warrior should be able to use a sword and a shield if they want and, as far as agro goes, it shouldn't even matter.<br>
<br>
That is just my stance. In my &quot;vision&quot; I see warriors using all types of weapons and shields and whatnot, not to hold agro, not for DPS, but for person preference based around their role playing stance and what type of &quot;warrior&quot; they consider themselves. Obviously if warrior A is weilding 2 weapons that are 2x better than warrior B's giant 2 handed broadsword, the monster will hate warrior A. But this should just make warrior B want to get the 2handed broadsword similar to Warrior A's 2 weapons which is readily available from the encounters Warrior A got his 2 weapons from. Keeping an equal playing field and varying choices to make sure warriors don't look like cookie cutouts.<br>
<br>
bleh?  <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showMessageRange?topicID=2517.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a><a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showMessageRange?topicID=2517.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a> <b>3</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showNextMessage?topicID=2517.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2517.topic&index=42><img src=http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/swaddreply.GIF border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.emailToFriend?topicID=2517.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.threadControl?topicID=2517.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2517.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2517.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub14.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="thesteelwarriorthearena">The Arena<option value="thesteelwarriorthebattlefield">The BattleField<option value="t